{
  "stem": "19807.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were sequestered there for five days, until-- they waited until the train that came to take us from Istanbul through Turkey, through the Steppes of Turkey, through Anatol, all the way through Syria.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember stopping in-- excuse me-- stopping in Aleppo, Syria, in which British soldiers gave us tea.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was amazing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, they were just getting from enriching and giving us tea.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And through Aleppo, we arrived-- the train ride from Istanbul to-- to Beirut was five or six days.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it was a-- it was almost a week.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then we arrived in Beirut.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then we were met by the-- some representative of the Jewish community there too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They took us by bus to-- to a hotel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We stayed overnight there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the next day, we boarded buses and were taken to Palestine, like a detention-- British detention camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it was not detention.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was more like quarantine camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "For about a week we stayed there until they checked our papers again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they-- the Israelis, at that time the Jews of Palestine came and they checked this out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In other words, if I was affiliated with Maccabi, that group went to one kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "If he was affiliated with the [NON-ENGLISH], they went to another kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So this is the way I wound up with our 40 people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We went to a kibbutz, a wonderful, wonderful, lovely place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Boys and girls.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Boys and girls together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, sadness and joy mixed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sadness we're leaving our parents, not knowing if we'll ever see them again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And joy that we're going to our new life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, after all, our lives were spared.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We're kids.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and again, we looked forward to Israel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- Palestine at the time.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
